The paper discusses automatic relation extraction (RE) using question-answer pairs as an indirect source of supervision. This falls under the field of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. Specifically, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as it covers NLP and information retrieval (IR) topics. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories as they cover machine learning and NLP topics. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible category as the paper discusses using knowledge bases and text features for RE. Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a less likely category but still relevant as the paper proposes a novel framework for RE using embeddings and a margin-based QA loss.
